<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="26Nov1940"><font color="red">26 November 1940</font> <i>Letters I</i> (to Paul Ruggiero): I sent a telegram to you and also to M. Augsbourg &hellip; the evening of the 20th, the same day &hellip; M. Augsbourg is the person chosen by the maison de sant&eacute; Pr&eacute;-Carr&eacute; to meet my daughter at the line of demarcation and accompany her in Switzerland. He came to S. G&eacute;rand on his own bat to see me and talk to me on the subject, being in France 8 or 10 days. I gave him the address of the Irish Legation &hellip; I telephoned this morning to the Irish Legation at Vichy. They told me that M. Augsbourg had not been to the Legation to see the Minister </div>
